bit_field.name: MAXMB
bit_field.description: Number Of The Last Message Buffer

bit_field_value.name: MCR_IDAM_one_full_ID
bit_field_value.description: Format A: One full ID (standard and extended) per ID filter table element.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_IDAM_two_full_ID
bit_field_value.description: Format B: Two full standard IDs or two partial 14-bit (standard and extended) IDs per ID filter table element.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_IDAM_four_partial_ID
bit_field_value.description: Format C: Four partial 8-bit standard IDs per ID filter table element.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_FDEN_CAN_FD_disabled
bit_field_value.description: CAN FD is disabled. FlexCAN is able to receive and transmit messages in CAN 2.0 format.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_FDEN_CAN_FD_enabled
bit_field_value.description: CAN FD is enabled. FlexCAN is able to receive and transmit messages in both CAN FD and CAN 2.0 formats.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_DMA_id2
bit_field_value.description: DMA feature for RX FIFO disabled.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_DMA_id4
bit_field_value.description: DMA feature for RX FIFO enabled.

bit_field.name: IRMQ
bit_field.description: Individual Rx Masking And Queue Enable

bit_field_value.name: MCR_IRMQ_individual_rx_masking_disabled
bit_field_value.description: Individual Rx masking and queue feature are disabled. For backward compatibility with legacy applications, the reading of C/S word locks the MB even if it is EMPTY.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_IRMQ_individual_rx_masking_enabled
bit_field_value.description: Individual Rx masking and queue feature are enabled.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_LPMACK_low_power_no
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is not in a low-power mode.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_LPMACK_low_power_yes
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is in a low-power mode.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_WRNEN_TWRNINT_RWRNINT_inactive
bit_field_value.description: TWRNINT and RWRNINT bits are zero, independent of the values in the error counters.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_WRNEN_TWRNINT_RWRNINT_active
bit_field_value.description: TWRNINT and RWRNINT bits are set when the respective error counter transitions from less than 96 to greater than or equal to 96.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_SUPV_id2
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is in User mode. Affected registers allow both Supervisor and Unrestricted accesses.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_SUPV_id4
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is in Supervisor mode. Affected registers allow only Supervisor access. Unrestricted access behaves as though the access was done to an unimplemented register location.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_FRZACK_freeze_mode_no
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN not in Freeze mode, prescaler running.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_FRZACK_freeze_mode_yes
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN in Freeze mode, prescaler stopped.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_SOFTRST_SOFTRST_reset_registers
bit_field_value.description: Resets the registers affected by soft reset.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_NOTRDY_id1
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN module is either in Normal mode, Listen-Only mode, or Loop-Back mode.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_NOTRDY_id4
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN module is either in Disable mode, Stop mode, or Freeze mode.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_HALT_HALT_enable
bit_field_value.description: Enters Freeze mode if the FRZ bit is asserted.

bit_field_value.name: MCR_FRZ_freeze_mode_disabled
bit_field_value.description: Not enabled to enter Freeze mode.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_LOM_listen_only_mode_enabled
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN module operates in Listen-Only mode.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_LBUF_highest_buffer_first
bit_field_value.description: Buffer with highest priority is transmitted first.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_LBUF_lowest_buffer_first
bit_field_value.description: Lowest number buffer is transmitted first.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_BOFFREC_auto_recover_enabled
bit_field_value.description: Automatic recovering from Bus Off state enabled.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_BOFFREC_auto_recover_disabled
bit_field_value.description: Automatic recovering from Bus Off state disabled.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_SMP_one_sample
bit_field_value.description: Just one sample is used to determine the bit value.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_SMP_three_sample
bit_field_value.description: Three samples are used to determine the value of the received bit: the regular one (sample point) and two preceding samples; a majority rule is used.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_CLKSRC_oscillator_clock
bit_field_value.description: The CAN engine clock source is the oscillator clock. Under this condition, the oscillator clock frequency must be lower than the bus clock.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL1_CLKSRC_peripheral_clock
bit_field_value.description: The CAN engine clock source is the peripheral clock.

bit_field.name: TXERRCNT_FAST
bit_field.description: Transmit Error Counter for fast bits

bit_field.name: RXERRCNT_FAST
bit_field.description: Receive Error Counter for fast bits

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_ERRINT_ENABLE
bit_field_value.description: Indicates setting of any error bit in the Error and Status register.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_BOFFINT_ENABLE
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN module entered Bus Off state.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_RX_DISABLE
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is not receiving a message.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_TX_transmit_message_no
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is not transmitting a message.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_RXWRN_RXERRCNT_GTE_96
bit_field_value.description: RXERRCNT is greater than or equal to 96.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_TXWRN_TXERRCNT_GTE_96
bit_field_value.description: TXERRCNT is greater than or equal to 96.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_STFERR_stuffing_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: A stuffing error occurred since last read of this register.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_FRMERR_form_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: A Form Error occurred since last read of this register.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_CRCERR_CRC_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: A CRC error occurred since last read of this register.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_ACKERR_ACK_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: An ACK error occurred since last read of this register.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_BIT0ERR_bit0_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: At least one bit sent as dominant is received as recessive.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_BIT1ERR_bit1_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: At least one bit sent as recessive is received as dominant.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_RWRNINT_Rx_warning_int_yes
bit_field_value.description: The Rx error counter transitioned from less than 96 to greater than or equal to 96.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_TWRNINT_Tx_warning_int_yes
bit_field_value.description: The Tx error counter transitioned from less than 96 to greater than or equal to 96.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_SYNCH_CAN_bus_sync_no
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is not synchronized to the CAN bus.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_SYNCH_CAN_bus_sync_yes
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN is synchronized to the CAN bus.

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_BOFFDONEINT_bus_off_done
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN module has completed Bus Off process.

bit_field.name: ERRINT_FAST
bit_field.description: Error interrupt for errors detected in Data Phase of CAN FD frames with BRS bit set

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_ERRINT_FAST_errors_data_phase_yes
bit_field_value.description: Indicates setting of any error bit detected in the data phase of CAN FD frames with the BRS bit set.

bit_field.name: STFERR_FAST
bit_field.description: Stuffing Error in the Data Phase of CAN FD frames with the BRS bit set

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_STFERR_FAST_stuffing_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: A stuffing error occurred since last read of this register.

bit_field.name: FRMERR_FAST
bit_field.description: Form Error in the Data Phase of CAN FD frames with the BRS bit set

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_FRMERR_FAST_form_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: A form error occurred since last read of this register.

bit_field.name: CRCERR_FAST
bit_field.description: Cyclic Redundancy Check Error in the CRC field of CAN FD frames with the BRS bit set

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_CRCERR_FAST_CRC_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: A CRC error occurred since last read of this register.

bit_field.name: BIT0ERR_FAST
bit_field.description: Bit0 Error in the Data Phase of CAN FD frames with the BRS bit set

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_BIT0ERR_FAST_bit0_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: At least one bit sent as dominant is received as recessive.

bit_field.name: BIT1ERR_FAST
bit_field.description: Bit1 Error in the Data Phase of CAN FD frames with the BRS bit set

bit_field_value.name: ESR1_BIT1ERR_FAST_bit1_error_yes
bit_field_value.description: At least one bit sent as recessive is received as dominant.

bit_field.name: BUF0I
bit_field.description: Buffer MB0 Interrupt Or Clear FIFO bit

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF0I_buffer_Tx_Rx_not_complete
bit_field_value.description: The corresponding buffer has no occurrence of successfully completed transmission or reception when MCR[RFEN]=0.

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF0I_buffer_Tx_Rx_complete
bit_field_value.description: The corresponding buffer has successfully completed transmission or reception when MCR[RFEN]=0.

bit_field.name: BUF4TO1I
bit_field.description: Buffer MB i Interrupt Or Reserved

bit_field.name: BUF5I
bit_field.description: Buffer MB5 Interrupt Or Frames available in Rx FIFO

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF5I_id2
bit_field_value.description: No occurrence of MB5 completing transmission/reception when MCR[RFEN]=0, or of frame(s) available in the FIFO, when MCR[RFEN]=1

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF5I_id4
bit_field_value.description: MB5 completed transmission/reception when MCR[RFEN]=0, or frame(s) available in the Rx FIFO when MCR[RFEN]=1. It generates a DMA request in case of MCR[RFEN] and MCR[DMA] are enabled.

bit_field.name: BUF6I
bit_field.description: Buffer MB6 Interrupt Or Rx FIFO Warning

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF6I_id2
bit_field_value.description: No occurrence of MB6 completing transmission/reception when MCR[RFEN]=0, or of Rx FIFO almost full when MCR[RFEN]=1

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF6I_id4
bit_field_value.description: MB6 completed transmission/reception when MCR[RFEN]=0, or Rx FIFO almost full when MCR[RFEN]=1

bit_field.name: BUF7I
bit_field.description: Buffer MB7 Interrupt Or Rx FIFO Overflow

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF7I_id2
bit_field_value.description: No occurrence of MB7 completing transmission/reception when MCR[RFEN]=0, or of Rx FIFO overflow when MCR[RFEN]=1

bit_field_value.name: IFLAG1_BUF7I_id4
bit_field_value.description: MB7 completed transmission/reception when MCR[RFEN]=0, or Rx FIFO overflow when MCR[RFEN]=1

bit_field_value.name: CTRL2_ISOCANFDEN_non_ISO
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN operates using the non-ISO CAN FD protocol.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL2_ISOCANFDEN_ISO
bit_field_value.description: FlexCAN operates using the ISO CAN FD protocol (ISO 11898-1).

bit_field.name: EACEN
bit_field.description: Entire Frame Arbitration Field Comparison Enable For Rx Mailboxes

bit_field_value.name: CTRL2_EACEN_RTR_compare_no
bit_field_value.description: Rx mailbox filter's IDE bit is always compared and RTR is never compared despite mask bits.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL2_EACEN_RTR_compare_yes
bit_field_value.description: Enables the comparison of both Rx mailbox filter's IDE and RTR bit with their corresponding bits within the incoming frame. Mask bits do apply.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL2_MRP_id2
bit_field_value.description: Matching starts from Rx FIFO or Enhanced Rx FIFO and continues on mailboxes.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL2_MRP_id4
bit_field_value.description: Matching starts from mailboxes and continues on Rx FIFO.

bit_field.name: ERRMSK_FAST
bit_field.description: Error Interrupt Mask for errors detected in the data phase of fast CAN FD frames

bit_field_value.name: ESR2_IMB_inactive_mailbox_no
bit_field_value.description: If ESR2[VPS] is asserted, the ESR2[LPTM] is not an inactive mailbox.

bit_field_value.name: ESR2_IMB_inactive_mailbox_yes
bit_field_value.description: If ESR2[VPS] is asserted, there is at least one inactive mailbox. LPTM content is the number of the first one.

bit_field_value.name: ESR2_VPS_invalid
bit_field_value.description: Contents of IMB and LPTM are invalid.

bit_field_value.name: ESR2_VPS_valid
bit_field_value.description: Contents of IMB and LPTM are valid.

bit_field_value.name: FDCTRL_TDCFAIL_in_range
bit_field_value.description: Measured loop delay is in range.

bit_field_value.name: FDCTRL_TDCFAIL_out_of_range
bit_field_value.description: Measured loop delay is out of range.

bit_field.name: MBDSR0
bit_field.description: Message Buffer Data Size for Region 0

bit_field.name: MBDSR1
bit_field.description: Message Buffer Data Size for Region 1

bit_field_value.name: FDCTRL_FDRATE_nominal
bit_field_value.description: Transmit a frame in nominal rate. The BRS bit in the Tx MB has no effect.

bit_field_value.name: FDCTRL_FDRATE_bit_rate_switching
bit_field_value.description: Transmit a frame with bit rate switching if the BRS bit in the Tx MB is recessive.
